marc hershman marine policy fellowship the leopold leadership program skip to main content search this site the leopold leadership program about fellows news fellowship information resources login fellowships positions early career environmental scholars new fellowships new positions marc hershman marine policy fellowship marc hershman marine policy fellowship academic level any level graduate student focus policy awards open to all duration year or less notes the hershman fellowship places one to three eligible graduate students or recent graduates with state agencies in olympia working on ocean and coastal science and management issues the program offers a first hand experience in crafting marine and natural resource policies and enables fellows to share their academic expertise with state decision makers fellows have previously worked or are currently working at the department of ecology department of natural resources department of health and military department emergency management division 2011 marks the end of the fellowship's three year pilot program which is currently under review under consideration is extending the fellowship from nine months to one year and broadening fellowship topics and placements deadline info fellowship detalis subject to change after 2011 awards check website for updated information 2012 leopold leadership program the stanford woods institute for the environment stanford university stanford ca 94305
